<br>
Tunare will call all living mobs to her aid if they are not cleared, so just about all the mobs must be killed. This requires 8+ hours by a raid force (force starts small and grows throughout the day)<br>
<br>
Things were going well. There were less than 15 mobs remaining to clear. Our engagement with Tunare was finally upon us after hour upon hour of clearing.<br>
<br>
Enter the Griefer.<br>
<br>
It's really quite simple to grief a Tunare raid. If you are not KOS, simply wait till the Plane is nearly cleared, zone in, walk through the nearly empty non-kos zone, and attack Tunare.<br>
<br>
You see, if Tunare is aggroed and not engaged, she will poof in around 30 minutes.<br>
<br>
That's right, you can have cleared the entire plain expending hundreds of man hours of work, and one unguilded level 47 ranger (Naturyl, in this case), can grief the whole thing away by poofing Tunare. <br>
<br>
He sat afk next to her, unresponsive to tells. When the time was right, he attacked her and died. Minutes later, he logged off naked in Bazaar. There was no &quot;oops&quot; no request for a rez from our force.<br>
<br>
Enter the do-nothing GM's.<br>
<br>
After the plane was completely cleared, and Tunare was gone, we got our expected answer. &quot;We are sorry but there is no proof that Tunare was maliciously despawned. We will not respawn Tunare. &quot; Thank you very much.<br>
<br>
So to recap:<br>
Tunare is a ridiculous time sink that requires several hundred man hours of work to finish. Nice encounter design.<br>
<br>
Any level 46 or above player can grief this encounter by poofing Tunare and really hurting a large number of players (it's a jerk's dream to be able to nail this many people at once). This goes way beyond training a raid or stealing loot.<br>
<br>
Tunare's coding to poof is a buggy insult and slap in the face to players. We are talking hundreds of hours of combined work disintegrating to shitty, callous code.<br>
<br>
It's ok with the GM's. They will not take action. They will not sanction the player. They will not restore Tunare.<br>
<br>
Thank you, Verant, for forever changing me from a defender of your customer service, to just another jaded player that is shocked whenever your GM's actually DO SOMETHING to help the players.<br>
<br>
So concludes my cross-server @#%$ You Griefers, Buggy Game, and Spineless, Do-nothing GM rant.<br>
